title: Justin Bieber wants his naked photos taken down, pronto
text:
Justin Bieber wants his naked photos taken down, pronto Compiled by Tony Hicks Posted: 10/09/2015 10:09:43 AM PDT Updated: 10/09/2015 10:11:03 AM PDT Justin Bieber's lawyers sent a cease-and-desist letter to the New York Daily News, demanding it take 20 nude photos of Bieber off its website. 
Apparently, someone hasn't figured out how this Internet thing works. 
Bieber was on vacation at the time with supposed new girlfriend, 20-tear-old British model Jayde Pierce, in Bora Bora. 
According to The Hollywood Report, the letter was sent Wednesday, demanding the pictures -- taken by paparazzi as Bieber strolled around his private pool -- be taken down within 12 hours. 
I would check and see if they complied, but that would mean looking at nude pictures of Justin Bieber. I don't like this job that much. 
Whew ... THR says they're still up. Justin Bieber performs during the Think It Up education initiative telecast for teachers and students, hosted by Entertainment Industry Foundation at Barker Hangar on September 11, 2015 in Santa Monica, California. (Photo by Christopher Polk/Getty Images For EIF) 
The boys at Bieber Legal say the photos violate the Beebs' privacy rights and infringe on his trademarks. 
I won't even ask, in this case, what "trademarks" mean. 
And, of course, they're threatening to sue. 
Yawn. Tony Hicks writes celebrity commentary for the Bay Area News Group. Contact him at Facebook.com/BayAreaNewsGroup.TonyHicks or Twitter.com/tonyhicks67 Advertisement
